-- Indian shares at over one-month closing high; Ranbaxy up after profit
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue Oct 28, 2014 06:07AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 28 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose on Tuesday to their highest close in more than a month, with drugmakers getting a boost after Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd <RANB.NS> reported its first profit in six quarters.

Lenders also extended recent gains on rising expectations the Reserve Bank of India would cut rates earlier than expected next year. State Bank of India <SBI.NS> provisionally rose 2.4 percent, while ICICI Bank Ltd <ICBK.NS> ended higher 1.8 percent. Ranbaxy unofficially surged 5.8 percent, while Sun Pharmaceutical Industries <SUN.NS>, which is in the process of acquiring it, rose x percent. [ID:nL4N0SN3VY]